  "texts": [
    "The Federal Rules of Civil Procedure specify three categories of cases which can be brought as class actions.",
    "Every class action case must fit into one of these three categories.",
    "Securities class action suits generally fall under one of the following two categories: 1.",
    "\"Common questions predominate over those affecting only individual members\" (Practical Law Securities Litigation & White Collar Crime 2023); or 2.",
    "A class action lawsuit is the most efficient and fair way of resolving the case (Practical Law Securities Litigation & White Collar Crime 2023)."
  ],
